  <static seed="8" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/PolynomialMultiplication/PolynomialMultiplication0.pg">
    <statement><p>Multiply the polynomials.</p>
<p><m>{8x}\left({x-4}\right)=</m><fillin characters="16" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>8x^{2}-32x</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>We multiply the monomial by each term in the binomial, using 
the properties of exponents to help us</p>
<p><m>\begin{aligned}
              {8x}({x-4})\amp ={8x^{2}-32x}
      \end{aligned}</m></p>
</solution>
